1
00:00:02,753 --> 00:00:05,422
VENDOR: Fish! Get your fresh fish!

2
00:00:07,424 --> 00:00:09,259
Ancient Rome!

3
00:00:12,346 --> 00:00:13,889
Well, not to them, obviously.

4
00:00:13,972 --> 00:00:17,559
To all intents and purposes, right now,
this is brand-new Rome.

5
00:00:17,643 --> 00:00:19,728
Oh, my God! It's...

6
00:00:20,312 --> 00:00:22,064
It's so Roman!

7
00:00:23,357 --> 00:00:25,192
This is fantastic.

8
00:00:26,068 --> 00:00:27,110
Ha, ha!

9
00:00:28,278 --> 00:00:29,947
I'm here!

10
00:00:30,531 --> 00:00:34,368
In Rome. Donna Noble, in Rome!

11
00:00:34,993 --> 00:00:38,121
This is just weird!
I mean, everyone here's dead.

12
00:00:38,205 --> 00:00:41,041
Well, don't go telling them that.

13
00:00:41,124 --> 00:00:44,628
Hold on a minute.
That sign over there is in English.

14
00:00:44,711 --> 00:00:46,547
Are you having me on? Are we in Epcot?

15
00:00:46,630 --> 00:00:48,924
No, no, no,
that's the Tardis translation circuits.

16
00:00:49,007 --> 00:00:51,134
Just makes it look like English.
Speech as well.

17
00:00:51,218 --> 00:00:53,512
-We're talking Latin right now.
-Seriously?

18
00:00:53,595 --> 00:00:56,598
-I just said "seriously” in Latin!
-Well, yeah.

19
00:00:57,057 --> 00:00:59,977
What if I said something
in actual Latin?

20
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:03,105
Like veni, vidi, vici. My dad said that
when he came back from football.

21
00:01:03,188 --> 00:01:06,775
If I said, "Veni, vidi, vici, "
to that lot, what would it sound like?

22
00:01:06,858 --> 00:01:09,570
I'm not sure. You have to think of
difficult questions, don't you?

23
00:01:09,653 --> 00:01:11,613
I'm going to try it!

24
00:01:12,489 --> 00:01:15,158
Hello, sweetheart.
What can I get you, my love?

25
00:01:15,325 --> 00:01:16,368
Um...

26
00:01:16,451 --> 00:01:18,328
Veni vidi vici.

27
00:01:18,453 --> 00:01:19,871
Huh? Sorry?

28
00:01:21,331 --> 00:01:26,128
(IN LOUD, SLOW VOICE)
Me no speak Celtic. No can do, missy.

29
00:01:26,211 --> 00:01:27,588
Yeah.

30
00:01:29,006 --> 00:01:33,010
-How's he mean, Celtic?
-Welsh. You sound Welsh.

31
00:01:33,093 --> 00:01:35,429
Well, there we are. Learnt something.

32
00:01:40,851 --> 00:01:45,105
-Don't our clothes look a bit odd?
-Nah! Ancient Rome, anything goes.

33
00:01:45,188 --> 00:01:47,482
It's like Soho, but bigger.

34
00:01:47,566 --> 00:01:50,485
-Have you been here before, then?
-Mmm, ages ago.

35
00:01:50,569 --> 00:01:53,697
Before you ask,
that fire had nothing to do with me.

36
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:57,034
Well, a little bit. But I never got
the chance to look around properly.

37
00:01:57,117 --> 00:02:01,413
Colosseum, Pantheon, Circus Maximus...

38
00:02:01,496 --> 00:02:04,374
You'd expect them to be looming by now.

39
00:02:04,458 --> 00:02:06,084
Where is everything?

40
00:02:07,127 --> 00:02:08,837
Try this way.

41
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:22,934
I'm not an expert,

42
00:02:23,018 --> 00:02:26,563
but there are seven hills of Rome,
aren't there?

43
00:02:26,647 --> 00:02:28,315
How come they've only got one?

44
00:02:28,398 --> 00:02:30,359
(RUMBLING)

45
00:02:30,442 --> 00:02:32,194
MAN: Here we go again!

46
00:02:35,906 --> 00:02:37,991
Wait a minute.

47
00:02:38,075 --> 00:02:42,496
One mountain, with smoke,
which makes this...

48
00:02:42,579 --> 00:02:44,456
Pompeii.

49
00:02:44,539 --> 00:02:46,416
We're in Pompeii.

50
00:02:47,209 --> 00:02:49,294
And it's volcano day!

51
00:02:50,087 --> 00:02:52,130
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

52
00:03:38,719 --> 00:03:42,055
I beg audience with
the High Priestess of the Sibylline.

53
00:03:42,139 --> 00:03:44,516
The High Priestess cannot be seen.

54
00:03:51,523 --> 00:03:53,191
What would you tell her, sister?

55
00:03:53,316 --> 00:03:56,611
It has come,
as foretold in the prophecy.

56
00:03:57,320 --> 00:04:00,031
The box. The blue box.

57
00:04:16,673 --> 00:04:18,175
You're kidding.

58
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:20,761
You're not telling me
the Tardis has gone.

59
00:04:20,844 --> 00:04:23,555
-Okay.
-Where is it, then?

60
00:04:23,638 --> 00:04:25,891
You told me not to tell you.

61
00:04:25,974 --> 00:04:28,518
Oi! Don't get clever in Latin.

62
00:04:28,602 --> 00:04:29,728
Um...

63
00:04:30,645 --> 00:04:32,022
Excuse me, excuse me!

64
00:04:32,147 --> 00:04:35,484
There was a box, a big, blue box.
A big, blue, wooden box just over there.

65
00:04:35,567 --> 00:04:38,195
-Where has it gone?
-Sold it, didn't I?

66
00:04:38,862 --> 00:04:41,406
But it wasn't yours to sell!

67
00:04:41,490 --> 00:04:45,869
It was on my patch, wasn't it?
I got 15 ses 30 for it. Lovely jubbly!

68
00:04:45,994 --> 00:04:48,121
-Who'd you sell it to?
-Old Caecilius.

69
00:04:48,205 --> 00:04:51,082
Look, if you want to argue,
why don't you take it up with him?

70
00:04:51,208 --> 00:04:53,627
He's on Foss Street.
Big fellow, can't miss him.

71
00:04:53,710 --> 00:04:55,045
Thanks!

72
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:58,173
What did he buy
a big, blue, wooden box for?

73
00:04:58,256 --> 00:05:00,300
Modern art!

74
00:05:00,383 --> 00:05:02,385
Out of the way! That's it!

75
00:05:02,886 --> 00:05:04,805
Oh, Rhombus, I'm a little bit peckish.

76
00:05:04,888 --> 00:05:07,432
Get me some ants in honey,
there's a good lad.

77
00:05:07,516 --> 00:05:10,227
Ooh! Maybe a dormouse?

78
00:05:14,189 --> 00:05:15,565
What do you think?

79
00:05:15,649 --> 00:05:19,361
You call it modern art, I call it
a blooming great waste of space.

80
00:05:19,444 --> 00:05:21,571
But we're going up in the world,
my love.

81
00:05:21,655 --> 00:05:24,574
Lucius Dextrus himself
is coming to the house this afternoon.

82
00:05:24,658 --> 00:05:26,785
What with that and our Evelina
about to be elevated...

83
00:05:26,910 --> 00:05:28,662
Oh, don't go on about it, Dad.

84
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:31,915
If we'd moved to Rome, like I said,
she could have been a vestal virgin.

85
00:05:31,998 --> 00:05:34,042
Someone mention vestal virgins?

86
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:37,254
Quintus, don't be so rude!
You apologise to the household gods!

87
00:05:37,379 --> 00:05:39,422
-Get off.
-Apologise right now.

88
00:05:39,506 --> 00:05:41,800
The gods are always watching.

89
00:05:44,803 --> 00:05:46,596
Positions!

90
00:06:02,696 --> 00:06:05,240
There. Now you've
made the heavens angry.

91
00:06:05,365 --> 00:06:07,117
Just say sorry.

92
00:06:08,076 --> 00:06:11,454
I tell you, Caecilius,
that boy will come to no good.

93
00:06:11,538 --> 00:06:13,748
Sorry, household gods.

94
00:06:13,832 --> 00:06:16,293
So where were you last night?
Down the thermapolium, I bet.

95
00:06:16,418 --> 00:06:19,588
Cavorting with Etruscans
and Christians and all sorts.

96
00:06:19,671 --> 00:06:21,089
How's your head, sunshine?

97
00:06:21,172 --> 00:06:23,800
-How's your head!
-All right, Dad, give us a break.

98
00:06:23,884 --> 00:06:25,802
You want to
smarten yourself up, Quintus,

99
00:06:25,927 --> 00:06:28,221
before Lucius Dextrus gets here.

100
00:06:28,305 --> 00:06:29,973
Look at your sister.

101
00:06:30,098 --> 00:06:32,434
She's giving us status.

102
00:06:32,517 --> 00:06:35,770
Oh, yeah, 'cause it's all about Evelina.

103
00:06:35,854 --> 00:06:38,064
She has the gift.

104
00:06:38,148 --> 00:06:39,941
Be proud of your sister for once.

105
00:06:40,025 --> 00:06:42,986
-Have you been consuming?
-Not this morning.

106
00:06:43,111 --> 00:06:45,864
Well, come on, sweetheart, practise!

107
00:06:45,947 --> 00:06:48,825
It's hot today,
the hypocaust is on full blast.

108
00:06:48,950 --> 00:06:50,911
The mountain god must be happy.

109
00:06:50,994 --> 00:06:53,872
Breathe deeply.
Remember what the sisterhood said.

110
00:06:57,334 --> 00:07:00,503
-It hurts.
-Oh, my love, is it too hot?

111
00:07:00,629 --> 00:07:02,672
Sometimes, in the smoke,

112
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:05,926
I see the most terrible things.

113
00:07:06,009 --> 00:07:07,677
Like what?

114
00:07:08,887 --> 00:07:10,221
A face.

115
00:07:11,723 --> 00:07:13,350
A face of stone.

116
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:15,727
It'll make sense. One day.

117
00:07:15,852 --> 00:07:17,854
Sister Spurrina promised.

118
00:07:17,938 --> 00:07:21,524
The veil will be parted,
and you'll be a seer.

119
00:07:39,209 --> 00:07:41,503
(GROWLING)

120
00:07:48,551 --> 00:07:50,387
Who are you?

121
00:07:52,555 --> 00:07:55,141
-Ha! I've got it! Foss Street, this way!
-No!

122
00:07:55,266 --> 00:07:57,227
I found this big
sort of amphitheatre thing.

123
00:07:57,352 --> 00:07:58,979
We can start there,
we could gather everyone together.

124
00:07:59,062 --> 00:08:01,064
They maybe have a great, big bell
or something we could ring.

125
00:08:01,189 --> 00:08:03,066
-Have they invented bells yet?
-What do you want a bell for?

126
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:05,568
To warn everyone, start the evacuation!

127
00:08:05,652 --> 00:08:07,404
What time does Vesuvius erupt?
When's it due?

128
00:08:07,529 --> 00:08:11,116
It's 79 AD, 23rd of August,
which makes volcano day tomorrow.

129
00:08:11,241 --> 00:08:13,243
Plenty of time.
We'll get everyone out easy!

130
00:08:13,326 --> 00:08:15,453
Yeah, except we're not going to.

131
00:08:15,537 --> 00:08:17,664
But that's what you do.
You're the Doctor, you save people.

132
00:08:17,747 --> 00:08:20,000
Not this time.
Pompeii is a fixed point in history.

133
00:08:20,083 --> 00:08:22,460
What happens, happens.
There is no stopping it.

134
00:08:22,585 --> 00:08:24,212
-Says who?
-Says me.

135
00:08:24,295 --> 00:08:26,339
-What, and you're in charge?
-Well, this Time Lord, yeah.

136
00:08:26,423 --> 00:08:29,467
Donna, human, no. I don't need
your permission, I'll tell them myself.

137
00:08:29,551 --> 00:08:31,553
If you stand in the marketplace
announcing the end of the world,

138
00:08:31,636 --> 00:08:33,471
they'll think
you're a mad old soothsayer.

139
00:08:33,596 --> 00:08:36,558
Now, come on! Tardis.
We are getting out of here!

140
00:08:36,641 --> 00:08:39,853
Well, I might just have something
to say about that, spaceman!

141
00:08:39,936 --> 00:08:41,855
Oh, I bet you will!

142
00:08:52,032 --> 00:08:55,785
The tall one, he calls us mad.

143
00:08:55,869 --> 00:09:00,165
Then he is a stranger to Pompe:ii.
Soon he will learn.

144
00:09:00,290 --> 00:09:02,500
We have found I, Sister Spurring,

145
00:09:02,625 --> 00:09:05,628
in the thirteenth book
of the Sibylline Oracles.

146
00:09:05,754 --> 00:09:07,797
The blue box.

147
00:09:07,881 --> 00:09:10,383
A temple made of wood,

148
00:09:10,467 --> 00:09:13,178
and yet the sibyl foretold
that the box would appear

149
00:09:13,303 --> 00:09:17,307
at the time of storms
and fire and betrayal.

150
00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:20,018
HIGH PRIESTESS: Sisters!

151
00:09:28,234 --> 00:09:29,861
Revered Mother, you should sleep.

152
00:09:29,986 --> 00:09:33,239
The Sibylline Oracles are wrong!

153
00:09:33,323 --> 00:09:36,326
But we have venerated her words
for generations.

154
00:09:36,409 --> 00:09:39,370
This is a new age.

155
00:09:39,454 --> 00:09:42,082
Heed my words.

156
00:09:42,624 --> 00:09:47,003
I predict a future
of prosperity and might,

157
00:09:47,087 --> 00:09:50,965
an endless empire of Pompeii,

158
00:09:51,049 --> 00:09:55,553
reaching out from this city
to topple Rome itself

159
00:09:55,637 --> 00:10:00,183
and encompass the whole wide world.

160
00:10:00,975 --> 00:10:05,522
If the disciples of the blue box
defy this prophecy,

161
00:10:05,647 --> 00:10:11,569
their blood will run
across the temple floor.

162
00:10:11,945 --> 00:10:13,029
(ALL GASP)

163
00:10:13,113 --> 00:10:15,365
The gods approve!

164
00:10:15,448 --> 00:10:17,367
Positions!

165
00:10:22,038 --> 00:10:23,289
Whoa!

166
00:10:24,666 --> 00:10:26,334
There you go.

167
00:10:26,417 --> 00:10:28,670
Thank you, kind sir.

168
00:10:28,753 --> 00:10:30,713
I'm afraid business
is closed for the day.

169
00:10:30,797 --> 00:10:33,133
-I'm expecting a visitor.
-Well, that's me, I'm a visitor.

170
00:10:33,216 --> 00:10:34,384
Hello!

171
00:10:35,301 --> 00:10:38,513
-Who are you?
-I am

172
00:10:38,596 --> 00:10:40,306
Spartacus.

173
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:43,017
-And so am L.
-Mr and Mrs Spartacus?

174
00:10:43,101 --> 00:10:44,769
-Oh, no, no, no. We're not married.
-Not together.

175
00:10:44,894 --> 00:10:47,647
Oh, brother and sister? Yes, of course!

176
00:10:47,730 --> 00:10:50,984
-You look very much alike.
-(BOTH) Really?

177
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:53,069
I'm sorry, but I'm not open for trading.

178
00:10:53,153 --> 00:10:55,822
-And that trade would be...?
-Marble.

179
00:10:55,905 --> 00:11:01,578
Lobus Caecilius, mining,
polishing and design thereof.

180
00:11:01,703 --> 00:11:03,788
-If you want marble, I'm your man.
-That's good.

181
00:11:03,872 --> 00:11:06,541
That's good,
"cause I'm the marble inspector.

182
00:11:06,624 --> 00:11:09,043
By the gods of commerce, an inspection!

183
00:11:09,127 --> 00:11:13,006
I'm sorry, sir,
I do apologise for my son.

184
00:11:13,089 --> 00:11:14,966
-QUINTUS: Oi!
-This is my good wife Metella.

185
00:11:15,049 --> 00:11:17,260
I must confess,
we're not prepared for...

186
00:11:17,343 --> 00:11:19,512
Nothing to worry about,
I'm sure you've got nothing to hide.

187
00:11:19,596 --> 00:11:23,433
Although, frankly, that object
looks rather like wood to me.

188
00:11:23,516 --> 00:11:25,602
I told you to get rid of it!

189
00:11:25,685 --> 00:11:27,353
I only bought it today!

190
00:11:27,437 --> 00:11:29,939
Ah, well. Caveat emptor.

191
00:11:30,023 --> 00:11:32,650
Oh, you're Celtic. There's lovely!

192
00:11:32,775 --> 00:11:35,528
I'm sure it's fine, but I might have to
take it off your hands

193
00:11:35,612 --> 00:11:36,988
for a proper inspection.

194
00:11:37,071 --> 00:11:40,617
While we're here, wouldn't you
recommend a holiday, Spartacus?

195
00:11:40,742 --> 00:11:42,827
Don't know what you mean, Spartacus.

196
00:11:42,911 --> 00:11:46,706
This lovely family,
mother and father and son,

197
00:11:46,789 --> 00:11:48,875
don't you think they should
get out of town?

198
00:11:48,958 --> 00:11:51,211
-Why should we do that?
-The volcano for starters.

199
00:11:51,294 --> 00:11:52,754
-What?
-The volcano.

200
00:11:52,837 --> 00:11:55,548
-The what-ano?
-The big volcano right on your doorstep.

201
00:11:55,632 --> 00:11:57,133
Oh, Spartacus, for shame!

202
00:11:57,258 --> 00:11:59,969
We haven't even greeted
the household gods yet.

203
00:12:00,053 --> 00:12:02,513
They don't know what it is.
Vesuvius is just a mountain to them.

204
00:12:02,639 --> 00:12:04,265
The top hasn't blown off yet.

205
00:12:04,349 --> 00:12:07,810
The Romans haven't even got a word
for "volcano”. Not until tomorrow.

206
00:12:07,894 --> 00:12:10,939
Oh, great. They can learn a new word.
As they die.

207
00:12:11,064 --> 00:12:12,482
Donna, stop it.

208
00:12:12,565 --> 00:12:15,276
I don't know what sort of kids you been
flying around with in outer space,

209
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:20,156
but you're not telling me to shut up.
That boy, how old is he, 167

210
00:12:20,281 --> 00:12:22,909
-And tomorrow he burns to death.
-And that's my fault?

211
00:12:22,992 --> 00:12:24,285
Right now, yes.

212
00:12:24,369 --> 00:12:28,164
Announcing Lucius Petrus Dextrus,

213
00:12:28,248 --> 00:12:30,833
chief augur of the city government.

214
00:12:35,088 --> 00:12:37,757
Lucius! My pleasure, as always.

215
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:39,592
Quintus, stand up.

216
00:12:39,884 --> 00:12:42,971
A rare and great honour, sir,
for you to come to my house.

217
00:12:44,889 --> 00:12:48,643
The birds are flying north
and the wind is in the west.

218
00:12:49,686 --> 00:12:52,480
Right, absolutely. That's good, is it?

219
00:12:52,605 --> 00:12:54,774
Only the grain of wheat knows
where it will grow.

220
00:12:54,857 --> 00:12:58,444
There now, Metella,
have you ever heard such wisdom?

221
00:12:58,528 --> 00:13:01,656
Never. It's an honour.

222
00:13:02,782 --> 00:13:07,537
Pardon me, sir, I have guests.
This is Spartacus and, uh, Spartacus.

223
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:09,998
A name is but a cloud
upon a summer wind.

224
00:13:10,081 --> 00:13:12,166
But the wind is felt
most keenly in the dark.

225
00:13:12,250 --> 00:13:13,876
Dark!

226
00:13:14,544 --> 00:13:18,131
But what is the dark
other than an omen of the sun?

227
00:13:18,214 --> 00:13:20,675
-I concede that every sun must set.
-Ha!

228
00:13:20,758 --> 00:13:23,177
And yet the son of the father
must also rise.

229
00:13:23,261 --> 00:13:28,308
Damn. Very clever, sir.
Evidently a man of learning.

230
00:13:28,391 --> 00:13:31,644
Oh, yes, but don't mind me.
Don't want to disturb the status quo.

231
00:13:31,728 --> 00:13:34,314
-He's Celtic.
-We'll be off in a minute.

232
00:13:34,397 --> 00:13:36,065
-I'm not going.
-It's ready, sir.

233
00:13:36,149 --> 00:13:37,775
-You've got to.
-Well, I'm not.

234
00:13:37,859 --> 00:13:40,278
The moment of revelation.

235
00:13:40,737 --> 00:13:44,449
And here it is,
exactly as you've specified.

236
00:13:44,532 --> 00:13:47,493
-It pleases you, sir?
-As the rain pleases the soil.

237
00:13:47,577 --> 00:13:50,330
Oh, now, that's different.
Who designed that, then?

238
00:13:50,538 --> 00:13:52,290
My lord Lucius was very specific.

239
00:13:52,415 --> 00:13:54,792
-Where'd you get the pattern?
-On the rain and mist and wind.

240
00:13:54,917 --> 00:13:57,253
-But that looks like a circuit.
-Made of stone.

241
00:13:57,337 --> 00:14:00,006
Do you mean you just
dreamt that thing up?

242
00:14:00,089 --> 00:14:02,425
That is my job as city augur.

243
00:14:02,508 --> 00:14:04,302
What's that, then, like the mayor?

244
00:14:04,427 --> 00:14:08,431
Oh, you must excuse my friend,
she's from Barcelona.

245
00:14:08,556 --> 00:14:11,851
This is an age of superstition,
of official superstition.

246
00:14:11,934 --> 00:14:14,562
The augur is paid by the city
to tell the future.

247
00:14:14,645 --> 00:14:16,064
"The wind will blow from the west."”

248
00:14:16,147 --> 00:14:17,690
That's the equivalent of
the ten o'clock news.

249
00:14:17,774 --> 00:14:20,443
They're laughing at us.

250
00:14:20,568 --> 00:14:24,489
Those two, they use words
like tricksters. They're mocking us.

251
00:14:24,572 --> 00:14:26,240
No, no, no, I meant no offence.

252
00:14:26,324 --> 00:14:29,952
I'm sorry, my daughter's been
consuming the vapours.

253
00:14:30,036 --> 00:14:32,580
By the gods, Mother,
what have you been doing to her?

254
00:14:32,663 --> 00:14:35,124
-Not now, Quintus.
-But she's sick. Just look at her!

255
00:14:35,291 --> 00:14:37,877
I gather I have a rival
in this household.

256
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:39,379
Another with the gift.

257
00:14:39,462 --> 00:14:42,590
Oh, she has been promised
to the Sibylline Sisterhood.

258
00:14:42,673 --> 00:14:44,801
They say she has remarkable visions.

259
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:47,345
The prophesies of women
are limited and dull.

260
00:14:47,470 --> 00:14:50,515
Only the menfolk have the capacity
for true perception.

261
00:14:50,598 --> 00:14:53,101
I'll tell you where the wind's
blowing right now, mate.

262
00:14:53,184 --> 00:14:55,019
(RUMBLING)

263
00:14:55,144 --> 00:14:58,898
The mountain god marks your words.
I'd be careful if I were you.

264
00:14:58,981 --> 00:15:00,650
Consuming the vapours, you say?

265
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:03,361
-They give me strength.
-It doesn't look like it to me.

266
00:15:03,444 --> 00:15:06,447
Is that your opinion as a doctor?

267
00:15:06,531 --> 00:15:09,283
- I beg your pardon?
-Doctor, that's your name.

268
00:15:09,492 --> 00:15:12,036
-How did you know that?
-And you.

269
00:15:13,246 --> 00:15:15,748
You call yourself "noble”.

270
00:15:15,832 --> 00:15:18,251
Now then, Evelina, don't be rude.

271
00:15:18,334 --> 00:15:22,588
-DOCTOR: No, no, not at all.
-You both come from so far away.

272
00:15:22,672 --> 00:15:26,300
A female soothsayer is inclined
to invent all sorts of vagaries.

273
00:15:26,384 --> 00:15:30,388
Oh, not this time, Lucius.
I reckon you've been out-soothsayed.

274
00:15:30,471 --> 00:15:32,640
Is that so?

275
00:15:32,723 --> 00:15:34,517
Man from Gallifrey.

276
00:15:35,101 --> 00:15:36,602
What?

277
00:15:36,686 --> 00:15:38,896
(FIERCE RUMBLING)

278
00:15:39,021 --> 00:15:40,898
The strangest of images.

279
00:15:40,982 --> 00:15:43,693
Your home is lost in fire, is it not?

280
00:15:43,776 --> 00:15:47,155
-Doctor, what are they doing?
-And you, daughter of

281
00:15:47,947 --> 00:15:49,824
-London.
-How does he know that?

282
00:15:49,907 --> 00:15:51,951
This is the gift of Pompeii.

283
00:15:52,034 --> 00:15:55,580
-Every single oracle tells the truth.
-That's impossible.

284
00:15:55,663 --> 00:15:59,041
Doctor, she is returning.

285
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:02,128
Who is? Who's "she"?

286
00:16:02,211 --> 00:16:04,881
And you, daughter of London,

287
00:16:06,340 --> 00:16:08,342
there is something on your back.

288
00:16:10,219 --> 00:16:14,140
-What's that mean?
-Even the word "Doctor" is false.

289
00:16:14,223 --> 00:16:17,101
Your real name is hidden.

290
00:16:17,226 --> 00:16:21,397
It burns in the stars,
in the cascade of Medusa herself.

291
00:16:22,398 --> 00:16:24,108
You are a lord, sir.

292
00:16:25,818 --> 00:16:28,237
A lord of time.

293
00:16:32,283 --> 00:16:33,993
Evelina!

294
00:16:38,039 --> 00:16:40,625
She didn't mean to be rude.

295
00:16:40,750 --> 00:16:43,085
She's ever such a good girl.

296
00:16:43,169 --> 00:16:46,839
But when the gods speak through her...

297
00:16:46,923 --> 00:16:49,717
-What's wrong with her arm?
-An irritation of the skin.

298
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:51,802
She never complains, bless her.

299
00:16:51,886 --> 00:16:55,097
-We bathe it in olive oil every night.
-What is it?

300
00:16:56,641 --> 00:16:59,519
Evelina said you'd come from far away.

301
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:03,439
Please, have you ever seen
anything like it?

302
00:17:13,157 --> 00:17:14,617
It's stone.

303
00:17:19,622 --> 00:17:21,457
(DOCTOR GRUNTING)

304
00:17:24,710 --> 00:17:26,295
Different sort of hypocaust.

305
00:17:26,379 --> 00:17:28,381
Oh, yes, we're very advanced in Pompeii.

306
00:17:28,464 --> 00:17:31,342
In Rome, they're still using
the old wood-burning furnaces,

307
00:17:31,425 --> 00:17:34,887
but we've got hot springs
heated from Vesuvius itself.

308
00:17:34,971 --> 00:17:37,557
-Who thought of that?
-The soothsayers.

309
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:40,268
After the great earthquake 17 years ago.

310
00:17:40,351 --> 00:17:44,063
An awful lot of damage. But we rebuilt.

311
00:17:44,146 --> 00:17:47,900
Didn't you think of moving away?
Oh, no, then again, San Francisco.

312
00:17:47,984 --> 00:17:50,486
That's a restaurant in Naples, isn't it?

313
00:17:50,570 --> 00:17:51,988
What's that noise?

314
00:17:52,071 --> 00:17:54,156
Don't know, happens all the time.

315
00:17:55,157 --> 00:17:58,077
They say the gods
of the underworld are stirring.

316
00:17:59,495 --> 00:18:01,497
But after the earthquake, let me guess,

317
00:18:01,581 --> 00:18:03,666
is that when the soothsayers
started making sense?

318
00:18:03,833 --> 00:18:05,751
Oh, yes, very much so.

319
00:18:05,835 --> 00:18:09,255
I mean, they had always been,
shall we say, imprecise.

320
00:18:09,338 --> 00:18:12,508
But then, the soothsayers, the augurs,
the haruspices, all of them,

321
00:18:12,633 --> 00:18:15,886
they saw the truth again and again.
It's quite amazing.

322
00:18:16,012 --> 00:18:19,015
They can predict crops and rainfall
with absolute precision.

323
00:18:19,140 --> 00:18:22,393
-Have they said anything about tomorrow?
-No.

324
00:18:22,518 --> 00:18:26,188
-Why, should they? Why do you ask?
-No, no, no reason, just asking.

325
00:18:26,314 --> 00:18:29,233
But the soothsayers,
they all consume the vapours?

326
00:18:29,317 --> 00:18:31,611
That's how they see.

327
00:18:31,694 --> 00:18:33,446
Ipso facto...

328
00:18:34,864 --> 00:18:36,198
Look, you...

329
00:18:37,325 --> 00:18:40,119
-They're all consuming this.
-Dust?

330
00:18:40,202 --> 00:18:42,204
Tiny particles of rock.

331
00:18:47,501 --> 00:18:49,128
They're breathing in Vesuvius.

332
00:18:53,841 --> 00:18:58,220
Quintus, me old son,
this Lucius Petrus Dextrus.

333
00:18:58,304 --> 00:19:01,349
-Where does he live?
-It's nothing to do with me.

334
00:19:01,432 --> 00:19:02,892
Let me try again.

335
00:19:03,017 --> 00:19:06,395
This Lucius Petrus Dextrus...

336
00:19:08,522 --> 00:19:09,732
Where does he live?

337
00:19:26,749 --> 00:19:28,834
Don't tell my dad.

338
00:19:30,795 --> 00:19:33,089
Only if you don't tell mine.

339
00:19:37,426 --> 00:19:39,220
Pass me that torch.

340
00:19:57,154 --> 00:20:00,700
The liar!
He told my father it was the only one.

341
00:20:00,783 --> 00:20:03,869
Well, plenty of marble merchants
in this town.

342
00:20:03,953 --> 00:20:06,997
Tell them all the same thing, get all
the components from different places

343
00:20:07,081 --> 00:20:08,708
so no one can see what you're building.

344
00:20:08,791 --> 00:20:11,419
-Which is what?
-The future, Doctor!

345
00:20:11,502 --> 00:20:15,381
We are building the future
as dictated by the gods.

346
00:20:18,467 --> 00:20:21,887
You're not supposed to laugh.
Thanks for that.

347
00:20:22,138 --> 00:20:24,140
What do you think?

348
00:20:24,223 --> 00:20:27,852
-The goddess Venus.
-(CHUCKLING) That's sacrilege!

349
00:20:27,977 --> 00:20:30,312
Nice to see you laugh, though.

350
00:20:31,814 --> 00:20:35,401
What do you do in old Pompeii, then,
girls your age?

351
00:20:35,484 --> 00:20:39,405
You got mates?
Do you go hanging about round the shops?

352
00:20:39,488 --> 00:20:41,532
TK Maximus?

353
00:20:41,657 --> 00:20:45,161
I am promised to the sisterhood
for the rest of my life.

354
00:20:45,244 --> 00:20:48,080
-Do you get any choice in that?
-It's not my decision.

355
00:20:48,164 --> 00:20:51,333
The sisters chose for me.
I have the gift of sight.

356
00:20:51,417 --> 00:20:54,754
Then what can you see
happening tomorrow?

357
00:20:54,879 --> 00:20:56,756
Is tomorrow special?

358
00:20:56,839 --> 00:20:58,632
You tell me.

359
00:20:58,716 --> 00:21:00,551
What do you see?

360
00:21:03,262 --> 00:21:07,433
The sun will rise, the sun will set.
Nothing special at all.

361
00:21:09,268 --> 00:21:13,773
Look, don't tell the Doctor
I said anything 'cause he'll kill me,

362
00:21:13,856 --> 00:21:16,275
but I've got a prophecy, too.

363
00:21:17,943 --> 00:21:20,446
DONNA: Evelina, I'm sorry,
but you've got to hear me out.

364
00:21:20,529 --> 00:21:23,741
-Sisters!
-DONNA: Evelina, can you hear me?

365
00:21:23,866 --> 00:21:25,367
Listen!

366
00:21:27,745 --> 00:21:29,663
EVELINA: There is only one prophecy!

367
00:21:29,747 --> 00:21:32,917
Everything I'm about
to say to you is true, I swear.

368
00:21:33,042 --> 00:21:34,794
Just listen to me.

369
00:21:34,877 --> 00:21:38,547
(ECHOING) Tomorrow
that mountain is going to explode.

370
00:21:38,631 --> 00:21:40,716
Evelina, please listen.

371
00:21:40,841 --> 00:21:44,261
The air is going to fill with
ash and rocks, tons and tons of it

372
00:21:44,386 --> 00:21:46,764
and this whole town
ls going to get buried.

373
00:21:46,889 --> 00:21:51,393
-EVELINA: That's not true.
-I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.

374
00:21:52,603 --> 00:21:54,021
But everyone's going to die.

375
00:21:54,104 --> 00:21:57,525
-A new prophecy!
-Impossible. There is only one.

376
00:21:57,650 --> 00:22:00,694
Even if you don't believe me, just
tell your family to get out of town.

377
00:22:00,820 --> 00:22:03,781
Just for one day, just for tomorrow,
but you've got to get out.

378
00:22:03,906 --> 00:22:07,159
-You've got to leave Pompeii.
-This is false prophecy!

379
00:22:12,581 --> 00:22:15,292
The Noble woman,
she spoke of a new prophecy,

380
00:22:15,376 --> 00:22:17,253
the fall of Pompeii.

381
00:22:17,378 --> 00:22:19,296
HIGH PRIESTESS:
Pompeii will last forever.

382
00:22:19,421 --> 00:22:23,759
-Then what must we do?
-The false prophet must die.

383
00:22:24,176 --> 00:22:25,970
Sacrifice her!

384
00:22:27,429 --> 00:22:30,391
Put this one there,

385
00:22:31,308 --> 00:22:33,185
this one

386
00:22:34,478 --> 00:22:37,147
there...Er, keep that one upside down.

387
00:22:37,273 --> 00:22:39,191
-What have you got?
-Enlighten me.

388
00:22:39,275 --> 00:22:41,694
What, the soothsayer doesn't know?

389
00:22:41,777 --> 00:22:44,113
The seed may float on the breeze
in any direction.

390
00:22:44,238 --> 00:22:47,658
Yeah, I knew you were going to say that.
But it's an energy converter.

391
00:22:47,783 --> 00:22:51,120
-An energy converter of what?
-I don't know.

392
00:22:51,203 --> 00:22:53,539
Isn't that brilliant?
I love not knowing, keeps me on my toes.

393
00:22:53,622 --> 00:22:55,666
It must be awful being a prophet.

394
00:22:55,791 --> 00:22:58,168
Waking up every morning,
"Is it raining? Yes, it is. I said so."

395
00:22:58,294 --> 00:23:01,255
Takes all the fun out of life.
But who designed this, Lucius?

396
00:23:01,338 --> 00:23:03,757
Hmm? Who gave you these instructions?

397
00:23:03,841 --> 00:23:05,301
I think you've babbled enough!

398
00:23:05,426 --> 00:23:08,387
Lucius, really, tell me. Honestly,
I'm on your side, I can help.

399
00:23:08,470 --> 00:23:10,347
You insult the gods!

400
00:23:10,472 --> 00:23:13,183
There can be only one sentence. At arms!

401
00:23:13,267 --> 00:23:15,436
(SPEAKING LATIN)

402
00:23:15,519 --> 00:23:16,854
Celtic prayers won't help you now.

403
00:23:16,979 --> 00:23:20,024
But it was him, sir, he made me do it.
Mr Dextrus, please don't.

404
00:23:20,149 --> 00:23:22,568
Come on now, Quintus, dignity in death.

405
00:23:22,651 --> 00:23:26,030
I respect your victory, Lucius.
Shake on it?

406
00:23:27,489 --> 00:23:29,116
Come on.

407
00:23:30,159 --> 00:23:32,286
Dying man's wish.

408
00:23:36,373 --> 00:23:38,626
-But he's...
-Show me.

409
00:23:41,670 --> 00:23:43,589
The work of the gods.

410
00:23:44,340 --> 00:23:46,800
-He's stone!
-Armless enough, though!

411
00:23:46,884 --> 00:23:48,510
DOCTOR: Quintus!

412
00:23:51,847 --> 00:23:53,265
The carvings!

413
00:23:53,349 --> 00:23:55,017
Run!

414
00:23:55,142 --> 00:23:56,852
My carvings!

415
00:23:57,937 --> 00:23:59,772
The work is unbroken.

416
00:23:59,855 --> 00:24:02,483
Oh, lord of the mountain, I beseech you.

417
00:24:02,566 --> 00:24:06,487
This man
would prevent the rise of Pompeii!

418
00:24:06,570 --> 00:24:09,156
(GROWLING)

419
00:24:09,239 --> 00:24:11,992
Lord, I beg of you, show yourself.

420
00:24:14,203 --> 00:24:16,121
Show yourself!

421
00:24:18,749 --> 00:24:20,417
(GROWLING)

422
00:24:23,921 --> 00:24:25,673
No sign of them.

423
00:24:25,756 --> 00:24:27,716
I think we're all right.

424
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:30,678
But his arm, Doctor...
Is that what's happening to Evelina?

425
00:24:30,803 --> 00:24:32,429
(POUNDING)

426
00:24:32,554 --> 00:24:34,598
What was that?

427
00:24:36,558 --> 00:24:38,185
The mountain?

428
00:24:38,268 --> 00:24:39,937
No, it's closer.

429
00:24:41,021 --> 00:24:42,898
(POUNDING INTENSIFIES)

430
00:24:47,820 --> 00:24:49,488
They're footsteps.

431
00:24:49,571 --> 00:24:51,281
It can't be.

432
00:24:53,617 --> 00:24:55,995
-Footsteps on the ground.
-What is it?

433
00:24:56,078 --> 00:24:57,579
What is it?

434
00:25:04,420 --> 00:25:07,256
What is it? What's that noise?

435
00:25:07,381 --> 00:25:09,174
That doesn't sound like Vesuvius.

436
00:25:09,258 --> 00:25:11,385
Caecilius? All of you, get out!

437
00:25:11,468 --> 00:25:13,804
-Doctor, what is it?
-Think we're being followed.

438
00:25:13,929 --> 00:25:15,806
(GROWLING)

439
00:25:17,307 --> 00:25:18,976
Just get out!

440
00:25:33,949 --> 00:25:35,617
The gods are with us.

441
00:25:35,701 --> 00:25:38,787
Water, we need water!
Quintus, all of you, get water! Donna!

442
00:25:38,871 --> 00:25:40,998
Blessed are we to see the gods!

443
00:25:43,333 --> 00:25:45,002
(CAECILIUS YELLING)

444
00:25:47,463 --> 00:25:49,882
Talk to me, that's all I want.

445
00:25:49,965 --> 00:25:53,635
Talk to me, just tell me who you are.
Don't hurt these people!

446
00:25:55,637 --> 00:25:57,514
Talk to me.

447
00:25:57,598 --> 00:26:00,350
I'm the Doctor.
Just tell me who you are.

448
00:26:22,998 --> 00:26:25,959
-What was it?
-A carapace of stone.

449
00:26:26,502 --> 00:26:29,254
Held together by internal magma.

450
00:26:29,338 --> 00:26:32,716
Not too difficult to stop, but I reckon
that's just the foot soldier.

451
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:37,429
Doctor, or whatever your name is,
you bring bad luck in this house.

452
00:26:37,513 --> 00:26:40,849
I thought your son was brilliant.
Aren't you gonna thank him?

453
00:26:43,685 --> 00:26:45,646
I don't know...

454
00:26:45,729 --> 00:26:49,441
If there are aliens at work in Pompeii,
it's a good thing we stayed.

455
00:26:49,525 --> 00:26:50,859
Donna!

456
00:26:52,027 --> 00:26:53,403
Donna?

457
00:26:54,655 --> 00:26:55,739
Donna!

458
00:26:56,323 --> 00:26:59,535
You have got to be kidding me.

459
00:26:59,868 --> 00:27:03,122
The false prophet will surrender
both her blood

460
00:27:03,956 --> 00:27:06,125
-and her breath.
-I'll surrender you in a minute.

461
00:27:06,208 --> 00:27:08,460
-Don't you dare.
-You will be silent.

462
00:27:08,544 --> 00:27:11,588
Listen, sister, you might have eyes
on the back of your hands,

463
00:27:11,672 --> 00:27:14,675
but you'll have eyes in the back of
your head by the time I finish with you.

464
00:27:14,758 --> 00:27:16,552
Let me go!

465
00:27:16,635 --> 00:27:20,722
This prattling voice will cease forever!

466
00:27:20,806 --> 00:27:23,058
DOCTOR: That'll be the day.

467
00:27:25,227 --> 00:27:28,147
No man is allowed to enter
the Temple of Sybil.

468
00:27:28,230 --> 00:27:32,025
Well, that's all right. Just us girls.
Do you know, I met the Sybil once?

469
00:27:32,109 --> 00:27:35,779
Hell of a woman. Blimey!
She can dance the tarantella.

470
00:27:35,863 --> 00:27:39,700
Nice teeth. Truth be told,
I think she had a bit of a thing for me.

471
00:27:39,783 --> 00:27:42,369
I said it'd never last.
She said, "I know." Well, she would.

472
00:27:42,452 --> 00:27:44,413
-You all right there?
-Never better.

473
00:27:44,538 --> 00:27:46,248
-I like the toga.
-Thank you.

474
00:27:46,331 --> 00:27:49,251
-And the ropes?
-Yeah, not so much.

475
00:27:50,836 --> 00:27:52,421
What magic is this?

476
00:27:52,504 --> 00:27:55,924
Let me tell you about the Sybil,
the founder of this religion.

477
00:27:56,008 --> 00:28:00,679
She would be ashamed of you.
All her wisdom and insight turned sour.

478
00:28:00,762 --> 00:28:03,348
Is that how you spread the word, eh?
On the blade of a knife?

479
00:28:03,432 --> 00:28:06,018
Yes, a knife that now welcomes you.

480
00:28:06,101 --> 00:28:08,478
HIGH PRIESTESS: Show me this man.

481
00:28:11,982 --> 00:28:14,359
High Priestess,
the stranger will defile us.

482
00:28:14,443 --> 00:28:19,031
Let me see. This one is different.
He carries starlight in his wake.

483
00:28:19,114 --> 00:28:20,616
Oh, very perceptive.

484
00:28:20,699 --> 00:28:22,910
Where do these words
of wisdom come from?

485
00:28:22,993 --> 00:28:24,703
HIGH PRIESTESS: The gods whisper to me.

486
00:28:24,786 --> 00:28:27,539
They've done far more than that.

487
00:28:27,623 --> 00:28:30,626
Might I beg audience?
Look upon the High Priestess.

488
00:28:33,295 --> 00:28:36,381
Oh, my God! What's happened to you?

489
00:28:36,465 --> 00:28:38,634
The heavens have blessed me.

490
00:28:38,717 --> 00:28:40,260
If I might...

491
00:28:46,808 --> 00:28:48,727
-Does it hurt?
-It is necessary.

492
00:28:48,810 --> 00:28:50,395
-Who told you that?
-The voices.

493
00:28:50,479 --> 00:28:53,023
Is that what's gonna happen to Evelina?

494
00:28:53,148 --> 00:28:55,567
Is this what's gonna happen
to all of you?

495
00:28:55,651 --> 00:28:57,903
The blessings are manifold.

496
00:29:00,864 --> 00:29:02,366
They're stone.

497
00:29:02,449 --> 00:29:03,951
Exactly.

498
00:29:04,993 --> 00:29:08,705
The people of Pompeii are turning
to stone before the volcano erupts.

499
00:29:08,789 --> 00:29:12,501
-But why?
-This word, this image in your mind,

500
00:29:12,584 --> 00:29:15,504
this volcano, what is that?

501
00:29:15,587 --> 00:29:18,298
More to the point,
why don't you know about it?

502
00:29:18,382 --> 00:29:22,052
-Who are you?
-High Priestess of the Sibylline.

503
00:29:22,135 --> 00:29:24,680
No, no, no, I'm talking to
the creature inside you.

504
00:29:24,846 --> 00:29:28,517
The thing that's seeding itself into
a human body, in the dust in the lungs.

505
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:31,937
Taking over the flesh
and turning it into what?

506
00:29:32,020 --> 00:29:34,690
Your knowledge is impossible.

507
00:29:34,773 --> 00:29:37,526
Oh, but you can read my mind.
You know it's not.

508
00:29:37,651 --> 00:29:39,945
I demand you tell me who you are!

509
00:29:40,028 --> 00:29:43,532
DEEP VOICE: We are awakening.

510
00:29:43,615 --> 00:29:45,617
The voice of the gods!

511
00:29:45,701 --> 00:29:48,495
ALL CHANTING:
Words of wisdom. Words of power.

512
00:29:48,578 --> 00:29:52,082
Words of wisdom. Words of power.
Words of wisdom...

513
00:29:52,165 --> 00:29:54,293
Name yourself. Planet of origin,

514
00:29:54,376 --> 00:29:56,295
galactic coordinates,
species designation,

515
00:29:56,378 --> 00:29:58,922
according to the universal ratification
of the Shadow Proclamation.

516
00:29:59,047 --> 00:30:03,593
We are rising!

517
00:30:03,677 --> 00:30:06,221
Tell me your name!

518
00:30:08,682 --> 00:30:11,893
Pyrovile!

519
00:30:13,979 --> 00:30:17,649
Pyrovile, Pyrovile, Pyrovile...

520
00:30:17,733 --> 00:30:20,277
-What's a Pyrovile?
-That's a Pyrovile. Growing inside her.

521
00:30:20,402 --> 00:30:22,654
-She's at halfway stage.
-What, and that turns into?

522
00:30:22,738 --> 00:30:24,781
That thing in the villa,
that was an adult Pyrovile.

523
00:30:24,865 --> 00:30:29,661
And the birth of a Pyrovile
will incinerate you, Doctor.

524
00:30:29,745 --> 00:30:33,290
I warn you. I'm armed.
Donna, get that grille open.

525
00:30:33,415 --> 00:30:35,334
-What the...
-Just...

526
00:30:36,460 --> 00:30:39,755
-What are the Pyrovile doing here?
-We fell from the heavens.

527
00:30:39,838 --> 00:30:42,924
We fell so far and so fast,
we were rendered into dust.

528
00:30:43,091 --> 00:30:45,344
Right. Creatures of stone
shatter on impact.

529
00:30:45,427 --> 00:30:46,928
When was that, 17 years ago?

530
00:30:47,012 --> 00:30:50,098
We have slept beneath
for thousands of years.

531
00:30:50,223 --> 00:30:52,267
Okay, so 17 years ago woke you up.

532
00:30:52,351 --> 00:30:54,519
And now you're using human bodies
to reconstitute yourself.

533
00:30:54,603 --> 00:30:56,104
But why the psychic powers?

534
00:30:56,188 --> 00:30:59,107
We opened their minds
and found such gifts.

535
00:30:59,191 --> 00:31:01,068
Fine, so you force yourself
inside a human brain,

536
00:31:01,151 --> 00:31:03,278
use their latent psychic talent,
I get that, yeah.

537
00:31:03,403 --> 00:31:05,614
But seeing the future,
that is way beyond psychic.

538
00:31:05,739 --> 00:31:07,282
You can see through time.

539
00:31:07,449 --> 00:31:10,285
Where does the gift
of prophecy come from?

540
00:31:10,369 --> 00:31:12,829
DONNA: I've got it.
DOCTOR: Now, get down.

541
00:31:12,913 --> 00:31:14,831
-What? Down there?
-Yes, down there.

542
00:31:14,956 --> 00:31:17,292
Why can't this lot predict the volcano?
Why is it being hidden?

543
00:31:17,376 --> 00:31:20,921
Sisters, I see into his mind.
The weapon is harmless.

544
00:31:21,755 --> 00:31:23,882
Yeah, but it's gotta sting.

545
00:31:30,013 --> 00:31:34,976
You fought her off with a water pistol.
I bloody love you!

546
00:31:35,894 --> 00:31:37,396
This way!

547
00:31:37,479 --> 00:31:39,815
-Where we going now?
-Into the volcano.

548
00:31:39,898 --> 00:31:41,691
-No way.
-Yes way.

549
00:31:41,817 --> 00:31:43,610
Have it your way.

550
00:31:44,611 --> 00:31:49,574
The stranger would threaten
our great endeavour.

551
00:31:49,658 --> 00:31:51,660
The time has come.

552
00:31:52,494 --> 00:31:57,124
The prophecy must advance!

553
00:31:57,332 --> 00:32:00,168
The prophecy must advance.

554
00:32:01,420 --> 00:32:03,255
Thy will be done.

555
00:32:04,714 --> 00:32:07,884
-Summon the Cult of Vulcan.
-Yes, sir.

556
00:32:08,009 --> 00:32:10,178
We must go to the mountain.

557
00:32:11,346 --> 00:32:13,348
Vesuvius awaits.

558
00:32:20,105 --> 00:32:22,065
Sunrise, my love.

559
00:32:23,191 --> 00:32:24,651
A new day.

560
00:32:25,318 --> 00:32:27,696
Even the longest night must end.

561
00:32:27,779 --> 00:32:30,073
But the mountain's worse than ever.

562
00:32:30,157 --> 00:32:34,161
We killed a messenger of the gods
in our own house.

563
00:32:34,244 --> 00:32:38,707
Sweetheart, can you see?
Tell us, what's going to happen?

564
00:32:38,832 --> 00:32:41,251
Just leave her alone.

565
00:32:46,548 --> 00:32:48,383
-I can see.
-What is it?

566
00:32:48,508 --> 00:32:50,594
A choice.

567
00:32:51,011 --> 00:32:53,430
Someone must make a choice.

568
00:32:57,934 --> 00:32:59,060
The most terrible choice.

569
00:33:00,770 --> 00:33:03,356
But if it's aliens
setting off the volcano,

570
00:33:03,440 --> 00:33:06,234
doesn't that make it all right
for you to stop it?

571
00:33:06,318 --> 00:33:08,487
DOCTOR: It's still part of history.

572
00:33:08,570 --> 00:33:10,780
DONNA: But I'm history to you.

573
00:33:10,864 --> 00:33:13,992
You saved me in 2008, you saved us all.
Why is that different?

574
00:33:14,075 --> 00:33:16,077
Some things are fixed,
some things are in flux.

575
00:33:16,203 --> 00:33:18,413
Pompeii is fixed.

576
00:33:18,497 --> 00:33:22,501
-How do you know which is which?
-Because that's how I see the universe.

577
00:33:22,584 --> 00:33:28,173
Every waking second I can see what is,
what was, what could be, what must not.

578
00:33:30,717 --> 00:33:33,178
It's the burden of a Time Lord, Donna.

579
00:33:36,139 --> 00:33:38,058
And I'm the only one left.

580
00:33:39,684 --> 00:33:42,604
-How many people died?
-Stop it!

581
00:33:42,687 --> 00:33:45,315
Doctor! How many people died?

582
00:33:45,398 --> 00:33:47,817
Twenty thousand.

583
00:33:47,943 --> 00:33:50,362
Is that what you can see, Doctor?

584
00:33:50,445 --> 00:33:52,197
All 20,0007

585
00:33:53,156 --> 00:33:55,242
And you think that's all right, do you?

586
00:33:55,325 --> 00:33:57,702
(PYROVILE WAILING)

587
00:33:57,786 --> 00:33:59,454
They know we're here. Come on!

588
00:34:11,675 --> 00:34:15,762
O mighty Vesuvius,
accept these offerings

589
00:34:16,221 --> 00:34:20,684
in Vulcan's design
and show unto us, I beseech you,

590
00:34:20,809 --> 00:34:22,769
the gods of the underworld!

591
00:34:22,852 --> 00:34:24,771
(ROARING)

592
00:34:55,927 --> 00:34:57,679
It's the heart of Vesuvius.

593
00:35:03,059 --> 00:35:05,353
We're right inside the mountain.

594
00:35:05,478 --> 00:35:07,063
There's tons of 'em.

595
00:35:07,188 --> 00:35:08,898
What's that thing?

596
00:35:09,899 --> 00:35:12,986
Well, you better hurry up and think of
something. Rocky IV's on its way.

597
00:35:13,069 --> 00:35:16,865
DOCTOR: That's how they arrive.
Or what's left of it. Escape pod.

598
00:35:17,198 --> 00:35:20,243
Prison ship. Gene bank.

599
00:35:21,036 --> 00:35:23,538
But why do they need a volcano?

600
00:35:23,622 --> 00:35:28,168
Maybe it erupts and they launch
themselves back into space or something.

601
00:35:28,251 --> 00:35:30,670
No, I think it's worse than that.

602
00:35:30,754 --> 00:35:32,422
How can it be worse?

603
00:35:32,547 --> 00:35:33,882
(ROARING)

604
00:35:34,007 --> 00:35:35,842
Doctor, it's getting closer.

605
00:35:35,925 --> 00:35:38,219
Heathens!

606
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:40,388
Defile us!

607
00:35:40,472 --> 00:35:43,975
They would desecrate your temple,
my lord gods!

608
00:35:44,392 --> 00:35:45,769
Come on.

609
00:35:45,852 --> 00:35:48,104
-We can't go in!
-Well, we can't go back.

610
00:35:49,606 --> 00:35:51,900
Crush them! Burn them!

611
00:35:52,651 --> 00:35:54,986
(PYROVILE ROARING)

612
00:36:13,630 --> 00:36:18,134
There's nowhere to run,
Doctor and daughter of London!

613
00:36:18,802 --> 00:36:22,555
Now then, Lucius, my Lord Pyrovillian.

614
00:36:22,681 --> 00:36:24,641
Don't get yourselves in a lava.

615
00:36:24,766 --> 00:36:26,643
-In a lava? No?
-No.

616
00:36:26,768 --> 00:36:30,438
But if I might beg the wisdom
of the gods before we perish.

617
00:36:31,439 --> 00:36:35,360
Once this new race of creatures
is complete, then what?

618
00:36:36,945 --> 00:36:40,740
My masters will follow the example
of Rome itself,

619
00:36:40,824 --> 00:36:45,912
an almighty empire,
bestriding the whole of civilisation!

620
00:36:45,995 --> 00:36:48,123
But if you've crashed,

621
00:36:48,248 --> 00:36:52,836
and you've got all this technology,
why don't you just go home?

622
00:36:52,919 --> 00:36:55,630
The heaven of Pyrovillia is gone.

623
00:36:55,714 --> 00:36:57,507
What do you mean, gone? Where's it gone?

624
00:36:57,590 --> 00:37:00,552
It was taken! Pyrovillia is lost.

625
00:37:00,635 --> 00:37:05,890
But there is heat enough in this world
for a new species to rise!

626
00:37:05,974 --> 00:37:08,476
Yeah, I should warn you.
It's 70 percent water out there.

627
00:37:08,560 --> 00:37:13,398
Water can boil
and everything will burn, Doctor!

628
00:37:13,481 --> 00:37:18,153
Then the whole planet is at stake.
Thank you, that's all I needed to know.

629
00:37:18,236 --> 00:37:19,988
DOCTOR: Donna!

630
00:37:23,825 --> 00:37:25,493
You have them, my lords.

631
00:37:28,496 --> 00:37:30,165
Could we be any more trapped?

632
00:37:37,672 --> 00:37:39,007
A little bit hot.

633
00:37:39,090 --> 00:37:42,343
See, the energy converter
takes the lava.

634
00:37:42,427 --> 00:37:45,513
Uses the power to create a fusion matrix
which welds Pyrovile to human.

635
00:37:45,597 --> 00:37:47,640
Now it's complete,
they can convert millions.

636
00:37:47,724 --> 00:37:49,768
Can't you change it with these controls?

637
00:37:49,893 --> 00:37:51,269
Of course I can. But don't you see?

638
00:37:51,352 --> 00:37:53,938
That's why the soothsayers
can't see the volcano.

639
00:37:54,022 --> 00:37:57,025
There is no volcano.
Vesuvius is never gonna erupt.

640
00:37:57,108 --> 00:37:59,319
The Pyrovile are stealing all its power.

641
00:37:59,402 --> 00:38:02,530
They're gonna use it
to take over the world.

642
00:38:02,614 --> 00:38:04,616
But you can change it back.

643
00:38:04,699 --> 00:38:08,953
Well, I can invert the system so that
the volcano will blow them up, yes,

644
00:38:09,037 --> 00:38:11,039
but that's the choice, Donna.

645
00:38:11,122 --> 00:38:13,917
It's Pompeii or the world.

646
00:38:14,042 --> 00:38:15,293
Oh, my God.

647
00:38:15,376 --> 00:38:19,547
If Pompeii is destroyed,
then it's not just history. It's me.

648
00:38:20,632 --> 00:38:22,091
I make it happen.

649
00:38:30,016 --> 00:38:32,644
But the Pyrovile are made of rocks.
Maybe they can't be blown up.

650
00:38:32,727 --> 00:38:35,730
Vesuvius exploded
with the force of 24 nuclear bombs.

651
00:38:35,814 --> 00:38:37,774
Nothing can survive it.

652
00:38:38,566 --> 00:38:40,568
Certainly not us.

653
00:38:42,987 --> 00:38:44,656
Never mind us.

654
00:38:50,870 --> 00:38:53,498
Push this lever and it's over.

655
00:38:56,042 --> 00:38:58,294
Twenty thousand people...

656
00:39:18,815 --> 00:39:22,193
No!

657
00:39:23,611 --> 00:39:26,281
No!

658
00:39:28,366 --> 00:39:30,577
(SCREAMING)

659
00:39:30,660 --> 00:39:32,161
A new prophecy!

660
00:39:32,287 --> 00:39:34,247
The future is changing.

661
00:40:00,356 --> 00:40:01,816
(DONNA SCREAMING)

662
00:40:11,200 --> 00:40:13,161
The sky is falling!

663
00:40:13,286 --> 00:40:16,414
Death. Only death!

664
00:40:26,174 --> 00:40:28,134
It was an escape pod.

665
00:40:48,279 --> 00:40:52,241
Out! Out! Everybody out! Quickly!

666
00:40:59,916 --> 00:41:02,585
(MAN SHOUTING)

667
00:41:13,888 --> 00:41:15,640
You lied to us!

668
00:41:17,642 --> 00:41:20,228
And yet this was meant to be.

669
00:41:23,773 --> 00:41:25,566
(ALL SCREAMING)

670
00:41:32,740 --> 00:41:34,867
(BABY CRYING)

671
00:41:34,951 --> 00:41:40,039
No, don't go to the beach!
Don't go to the beach! Go to the hills!

672
00:41:40,206 --> 00:41:43,960
Listen to me!
Don't go to the beach! It's not safe!

673
00:41:44,043 --> 00:41:45,503
Listen to me!

674
00:41:45,586 --> 00:41:46,754
(CHILD CRYING)

675
00:41:46,838 --> 00:41:49,048
-Come here.
-MOTHER: Give him to me!

676
00:41:53,094 --> 00:41:55,054
Come on.

677
00:42:05,690 --> 00:42:07,942
You can't save us, Doctor.

678
00:42:15,992 --> 00:42:17,326
No!

679
00:42:19,620 --> 00:42:21,497
Doctor, you can't!

680
00:42:27,462 --> 00:42:29,088
Doctor!

681
00:42:53,488 --> 00:42:55,907
You can't just leave them!

682
00:42:55,990 --> 00:42:58,201
Don't you think I've done enough?

683
00:42:58,284 --> 00:43:01,370
History is back in place
and everyone dies.

684
00:43:02,163 --> 00:43:06,667
You've got to go back! Doctor, I'm
telling you, take this thing back!

685
00:43:16,803 --> 00:43:19,055
It's not fair.

686
00:43:19,138 --> 00:43:21,015
No, it's not.

687
00:43:22,350 --> 00:43:26,771
But your own planet. It burned.

688
00:43:27,730 --> 00:43:30,691
That's just it. Don't you see, Donna?
Can't you understand?

689
00:43:30,775 --> 00:43:34,612
If I could go back and save them,
then I would. But I can't.

690
00:43:38,407 --> 00:43:42,411
I can never go back. I can't.
I just can't. I can't.

691
00:43:42,537 --> 00:43:45,873
Just someone. Please.

692
00:43:48,709 --> 00:43:52,380
Not the whole town. Just save someone.

693
00:44:11,149 --> 00:44:12,984
(WHOOSHING)

694
00:44:34,922 --> 00:44:36,549
Come with me.

695
00:45:01,407 --> 00:45:03,743
It's never forgotten, Caecilius.

696
00:45:05,036 --> 00:45:09,832
Oh, time will pass, man will move on
and stories will fade, but one day,

697
00:45:11,667 --> 00:45:14,045
Pompeii will be found again.

698
00:45:15,087 --> 00:45:16,964
In thousands of years.

699
00:45:20,968 --> 00:45:23,054
And everyone will remember you.

700
00:45:31,229 --> 00:45:34,815
What about you, Evelina?
Can you see anything?

701
00:45:38,986 --> 00:45:41,030
The visions have gone.

702
00:45:41,113 --> 00:45:45,201
The explosion was so powerful,
it cracked open a rift in time.

703
00:45:45,284 --> 00:45:48,537
Just for a second. That's what gave you
the gift of prophecy.

704
00:45:48,621 --> 00:45:52,625
It echoed back
into the Pyrovillian alternative.

705
00:45:54,085 --> 00:45:56,504
But not any more.

706
00:45:56,587 --> 00:45:58,506
You're free.

707
00:46:01,342 --> 00:46:05,763
But tell me, who are you, Doctor?

708
00:46:06,639 --> 00:46:10,851
With your words and your temple
containing such size within.

709
00:46:10,935 --> 00:46:12,770
Oh, I was never here.

710
00:46:13,854 --> 00:46:15,731
Don't tell anyone.

711
00:46:17,358 --> 00:46:21,153
The great god Vulcan must be enraged.

712
00:46:24,031 --> 00:46:25,783
It's so volcanic.

713
00:46:30,162 --> 00:46:34,292
It's like some sort of...volcano.

714
00:46:39,547 --> 00:46:41,215
All of those people.

715
00:47:33,267 --> 00:47:34,977
Thank you.

716
00:47:35,561 --> 00:47:36,854
Yeah.

717
00:47:41,984 --> 00:47:44,195
You were right.

718
00:47:44,278 --> 00:47:46,447
Sometimes I need someone.

719
00:47:49,116 --> 00:47:51,452
Welcome aboard.

720
00:47:51,535 --> 00:47:53,037
Yeah.

721
00:48:07,051 --> 00:48:10,012
Metella, my love,
have you seen that clasp?

722
00:48:10,137 --> 00:48:13,307
The beetle one.
The Egyptians do love a scarab.

723
00:48:13,391 --> 00:48:17,186
Here we are. I was giving it a polish.
Now calm down.

724
00:48:17,311 --> 00:48:20,981
If I get that contract
for the marble granaries of Alexandria,

725
00:48:21,065 --> 00:48:22,858
we'll be rich. You'll see.

726
00:48:22,983 --> 00:48:24,944
Hold on there, Evelina.

727
00:48:25,027 --> 00:48:27,405
You are not going out wearing that!

728
00:48:27,488 --> 00:48:31,409
Don't start, Dad. It's what
all the girls in Rome are wearing.

729
00:48:31,492 --> 00:48:32,993
I'll see you later.

730
00:48:33,953 --> 00:48:35,788
Are you seeing that boy again?

731
00:48:35,871 --> 00:48:39,250
Oh, look at Quintus. My son, the doctor.

732
00:48:39,333 --> 00:48:42,128
Mum, I've told you.
I'm not a doctor. Not yet.

733
00:48:42,211 --> 00:48:44,255
I'm just a student
of the physical sciences.

734
00:48:44,338 --> 00:48:46,465
Well, that's a doctor to me.

735
00:48:47,383 --> 00:48:51,470
Give thanks to the household gods
before you go. There's a good boy.

736
00:48:52,346 --> 00:48:56,183
Come here, let me fix it.
You've got that folded all wrong.

737
00:48:59,228 --> 00:49:01,355
Thank you, household gods.

738
00:49:02,189 --> 00:49:04,066
Thank you for everything.

739
00:49:15,035 --> 00:49:17,621
Now then, Dr Noble, Mrs Noble,
if you'd like to come with me?

740
00:49:17,705 --> 00:49:19,957
-Oh, no, no. We're not married.
-We're so not married.

741
00:49:20,040 --> 00:49:21,167
-Never.
-Never, ever.

742
00:49:21,250 --> 00:49:25,880
Here at Ood Operations we like to think
of the Ood as our trusted friends.

743
00:49:25,963 --> 00:49:27,381
I've found your unwanted guests.

744
00:49:27,465 --> 00:49:29,008
Because at heart, what is an Ood...

745
00:49:29,091 --> 00:49:30,217
I'm on your side!

746
00:49:30,301 --> 00:49:31,802
...but a reflection of us?

747
00:49:31,886 --> 00:49:32,970
It's a revolution.

748
00:49:33,053 --> 00:49:34,305
If your Ood is happy...

749
00:49:34,388 --> 00:49:35,890
The circle must be broken.

750
00:49:36,015 --> 00:49:37,475
What is it? What is the circle?

751
00:49:37,558 --> 00:49:39,018
...then you'll be happy, too.

752
00:49:39,810 --> 00:49:41,520
MAN: Shoot to kill!

753
00:49:41,854 --> 00:49:44,398
-Doctor, Donna. Friends!
-The circle must be broken!

